      <h1 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:clamp(2rem,5vw,3.25rem);font-weight:400;color:#f0ece4;line-height:1.12;letter-spacing:-0.02em;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        Settlement Default in Queensland: What Happens When the Buyer or Seller Fails to Complete on the Agreed Day
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        Settlement default is uncommon, but when it happens it changes the rules quickly. Time becomes critical, the contract clauses sellers and buyers ignored at signing suddenly matter, and the next 14 days dictate the outcome.
      </p>
